    • Method Detail

      • listen

        public void listen(java.lang.Object other)
        Description copied from interface: Cell
        Listen for changes in a reference. A reference can be a single Cell or several cells in a Range. For every cell in a Range, this Cell subscribes as listener, and the other cell is appended to the references Vector for this Cell.
        Specified by:
        listen in interface Cell
        Parameters:
        other - Another Cell instance, or Range containing cells.

      • update

        void update(java.util.Stack<Cell> tree,
          java.util.Vector<Cell> calculated)
      throws java.lang.Exception
        - Preparese the input for this cell to fetch the references, the result might be incorrect. - Update these references recursively, and check for cross references the current tree (this > reference > reference). If a cross reference conflict occurs, set the values for this tree and relations to "#VALUE" - Update the listeners recursively, if a cross reference conflict occurs, set the values for this tree and relations to "#VALUE"
        Parameters:
        tree - Path from origin to the current cell to check cross references against
        calculated - Cells calculated in this update to prevent infinite updating of listeners
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception
